body.p: Reference: Nielsen et al; Biophys. Chem. (1998) 72:49-62

specific flow rates (in reactorvolume/seconds):
flow = 1.1e-2 : periodic oscillations
flow = 8.25e-3 : complex periodic oscillations
flow = 8.154e-3 : complex periodic oscillations
flow = 1e-3 : harmonic periodic oscillations
V4 = 10 mM/s instead of 20 in the paper, in order to reproduce the figures.
we can reproduce the results from the paper only If we interpret the *seconds* for the constants from table 2 as *minutes* (to correspond to the flow units in figure 9)
Initial amounts are taken from a version of the model on JWS Online because table 3 of the paper contains only the input flows for the reactor and no initial conditions for the various species.
